com.rhizospherejs.gwt.client.renderer
Interface RenderingOutput

All Known Implementing Classes:
RenderingOutputImpl
public interface RenderingOutput

Helper interface that RhizosphereRenderer instances use to emit and customize the renderings they produce.

battlehorse@google.com (Riccardo Govoni)

emitElement

void emitElement(com.google.gwt.dom.client.Element element)
Invoked by renderers that emit their renderings as HTML elements. Renderers must invoke exactly one of the emit methods ( emitElement(Element), emitHTML(String), emitSafeHtml(SafeHtml) or emitWidget(Widget)) just once per rendering.

addDragHandler

void addDragHandler(com.google.gwt.dom.client.Element dragHandler)
Registers an element as drag handler.

Renderings produced by a renderer can be dragged within the Rhizosphere user interface. By default, the user can drag a rendering by starting the drag operation from any point within the rendering (the entire rendering act as a drag handler). This may cause some conflicts in mouse event handling depending on the contents of the rendering.

Renderings can therefore have custom drag handlers. To use custom drag handlers have the renderer class implement the HasCustomDragHandlers interface and invoke this method on any element that should act as drag handler.

Parameters:
dragHandler - An element that can act as drag handler.
